<inglise> Commission Regulation (EC) No 2602/2000 of 17 November 2000 laying down detailed rules for the implementation of Council Regulation (EC) No 2494/95 as regards minimum standards for the treatment of price reductions in the Harmonised Index of Consumer Prices (Text with EEA relevance) </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2602/2000, millega kehtestatakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksites hinnaalanduste k&auml;sitlemise miinimumstandardite kohta 17. november 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> (EMPs kohaldatav tekst) EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2494/95 of 23 October 1995 concerning harmonised indices of consumer prices(1), and in particular Article 4 in conjunction with Article 5(3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 23. oktoobri 1995. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksite kohta, (1) eriti selle artiklit 4 ja artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> After consulting the European Central Bank(2), </inglise>
<eesti> olles n&otilde;u pidanud Euroopa Keskpangaga (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) By virtue of Article 5(1) (b) of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95, each Member State is required to produce a Harmonised Index of Consumer Prices (HICP) starting with the index for January 1997. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti b kohaselt peab iga liikmesriik koostama &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksi (HICP) alates 1997. aasta jaanuari indeksist; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) There is considerable scope for procedural differences in the treatment of price reductions and the relationship between price reductions and purchase price. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) hinnaalandusi ning hinnaalanduste ja ostuhinna suhet v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitleda v&auml;ga erinevalt. </eesti>
<inglise> A harmonised methodology for the treatment of price reductions in the HICP is necessary to ensure that the resulting HICPs meet the comparability requirement of Article 4 of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95. </inglise>
<eesti> HICPs kasutatavate hinnaalanduste k&auml;sitlemiseks on vaja &uuml;htlustatud meetodeid, et tagada saadavate HICPde vastavus m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artikli 4 kohasele v&otilde;rreldavusn&otilde;udele. </eesti>
<inglise> It will also improve their reliability and relevance. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti parandab see nende usaldatavust ja asjakohasust; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Prices used in the HICP should be purchaser prices actually paid by households to purchase individual goods and services in monetary transactions, including any taxes less subsidies on the products, after deductions for discounts for bulk or off-peak purchases from standard prices or charges, and excluding interest or services charges added under credit arrangements and any extra charges incurred as a result of failing to pay within the period stated at the time the purchases were made. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) HICPs kasutatavad hinnad peaksid olema leibkondade tegelikult makstud ostuhinnad &uuml;ksikkaupade ostmiseks rahalistes tehingutes, kaasa arvatud k&otilde;ik toodete suhtes kohaldatavad maksud ilma subsiidiumideta p&auml;rast hulgi- v&otilde;i v&auml;hese tarbimise mahaarvamisi standardhindadest v&otilde;i -tasudest ning v&auml;lja arvatud krediidikokkulepete intressi- v&otilde;i teenustasud ja k&otilde;ik lisatasud, mis tulenevad suutmatusest maksta ostuhetkel kokkulepitud t&auml;htaja jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) In the event of changes in specification, prices should be treated in accordance with the rules regarding quality adjustment set out in Commission Regulation (EC) No 1749/96 of 9 September 1996 on initial implementing measures for Council Regulation (EC) No 2494/95 concerning harmonised indices of consumer prices(3), as last amended by Council Regulation (EC) No 1688/98(4). </inglise>
<eesti> 4) tunnusjoonte muutumise korral tuleks hindu k&auml;sitleda vastavalt kvaliteedikohandamist k&auml;sitlevatele eeskirjadele, mis on ette n&auml;htud komisjoni 9. septembri 1996. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 1749/96 &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindekseid k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 esialgsete rakendusmeetmete kohta, (3) viimati muudetud n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1688/98 (4); </eesti>
<inglise> (5) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Statistical Programme Committee (SPC) established by Council Decision 89/382/EEC, Euratom(5), </inglise>
<eesti> 5) k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las n&otilde;ukogu otsusega 89/382/EM&Uuml;, Euratom (5) loodud statistikaprogrammi komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Aim </inglise>
<eesti> Eesm&auml;rk </eesti>
<inglise> The aim of this Regulation is to specify the treatment in the Harmonised Index of Consumer Prices, hereinafter referred to as "HICP" of reductions in prices for individual goods or services in order to ensure that HICPs are reliable and relevant and meet the comparability requirements laid down in Article 4 of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse eesm&auml;rk on t&auml;psustada, kuidas k&auml;sitleda &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksis, edaspidi "HICP", &uuml;ksikkaupade v&otilde;i -teenuste hinnaalandusi tagamaks, et HICPd oleksid usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsed ja asjakohased ning vastaksid m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artiklis 4 s&auml;testatud v&otilde;rreldavusn&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Purchaser prices </inglise>
<eesti> Ostuhinnad </eesti>
<inglise> Unless otherwise stated purchaser prices used in the HICP shall in general take account of reductions in prices of individual goods and services if such reductions: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui pole s&auml;testatud teisiti, arvestavad HICPs kasutatavad ostuhinnad &uuml;ldiselt &uuml;ksikkaupade ja -teenuste hinnaalandusi, kui need hinnaalandused: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) can be attributed to the purchase of an individual good or service; </inglise>
<eesti> a) on seostatavad konkreetse kauba v&otilde;i teenuse ostmisega; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) are available to all potential consumers with no special conditions attached (non-discriminatory); </inglise>
<eesti> b) on k&auml;ttesaadavad k&otilde;igile v&otilde;imalikele tarbijatele ilma mingite eritingimusteta (mittediskrimineerivad); </eesti>
<inglise> (c) are known to the purchaser at the time when they enter into the agreement with the seller to purchase the product concerned; and </inglise>
<eesti> c) on ostjale teada ajal, kui ta s&otilde;lmib m&uuml;&uuml;jaga kokkuleppe asjakohase toote ostmiseks; ja </eesti>
<inglise> (d) can be claimed at the time of purchase or within such a time period following the actual purchase that they might be expected to have a significant influence on the quantities purchasers are willing to purchase. </inglise>
<eesti> d) neid v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda ostmise ajal v&otilde;i sellisel ajavahemikul p&auml;rast tegelikku ostmist, nii et neil on eeldatavasti m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rne m&otilde;ju kogustele, mida ostjad soovivad osta. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, reductions in the prices of individual goods and services which are likely or expected to be available again at standard prices or are available elsewhere at standard prices shall be taken into account in the HICP. </inglise>
<eesti> Eriti v&otilde;etakse HICPs arvesse &uuml;ksikkaupade ja -teenuste hinnaalandusi, mis on edaspidi usutavasti v&otilde;i eeldatavasti j&auml;lle k&auml;ttesaadavad standardhinnaga v&otilde;i on mujal k&auml;ttesaadavad standardhinnaga. </eesti>
<inglise> Standard price means the price without any conditions or qualifications and not described as a special price. </inglise>
<eesti> Standardhind on ilma mingite tingimuste v&otilde;i reservatsioonideta hind, mida ei kirjeldata kui erihinda. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Inducements </inglise>
<eesti> Ajendid </eesti>
<inglise> The market value of something temporarily offered to consumers to persuade them to purchase a particular product, hereinafter referred to as an "inducement", may be deducted if known. </inglise>
<eesti> Millegi ajutiselt tarbijatele pakutava, millega neid kallutatakse konkreetset toodet ostma, edaspidi "ajendi", turuv&auml;&auml;rtuse v&otilde;ib maha arvata, kui see on teada. </eesti>
<inglise> That market value shall be added back at the time the offer is withdrawn. </inglise>
<eesti> See turuv&auml;&auml;rtus lisatakse tagasi, kui pakkumine l&otilde;peb. </eesti>
<inglise> Inducements in the form of extras, such as extra quantity of the product concerned, inclusion of a different product "free of charge" or other benefits, shall be disregarded if they are not significant. </inglise>
<eesti> Ajendid lisadena nagu t&auml;iendav kogus k&otilde;nealust toodet, teise toote lisamine "tasuta" v&otilde;i muud soodustused j&auml;etakse t&auml;helepanuta, kui need ei ole m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rsed. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Specification change </inglise>
<eesti> Tunnusjoonte muutus </eesti>
<inglise> Where specification changes, prices shall be treated in accordance with the rules on specification changes, and in particular those regarding quality adjustment in Article 5 of Regulation (EC) No 1749/96. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tunnusjooned muutuvad, k&auml;ideldakse hindu vastavalt tunnusjoonte muutumise eeskirjadele, eelk&otilde;ige vastavalt kvaliteedikohandamise eeskirjadele, mis on s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1749/96 artiklis 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Implementation </inglise>
<eesti> Rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of this Regulation shall be applied by Member States in December 2000 at the latest and take effect either with the index for January 2001 or with the index for January 2002. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kohaldavad k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tteid hiljemalt detsembris 2000 ja need j&otilde;ustuvad 2001. aasta jaanuari v&otilde;i 2002. aasta jaanuari indeksi suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Revision </inglise>
<eesti> L&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> As a transitional measure, where the implementation of the provisions of this Regulation affects the annual rate of change (m/(m-12)) of the all-items index by more than one-tenth of one percentage point compared with an index which does not take account of price reductions, the index series concerned shall be revised appropriately. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse rakendamine m&otilde;jutab k&otilde;igi punktide indeksi iga-aastast muutust (m/(m-12)) rohkem kui &uuml;he k&uuml;mnendiku protsendi v&otilde;rra v&otilde;rreldes indeksiga, mis ei arvesta hinnaalandusi, vaadatakse asjakohane indeksiseeria &uuml;leminekumeetmena kohaselt l&auml;bi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> General provisions relating to the revisions policy for the HICPs shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 14 of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95, whereupon the transitional measures shall cease to apply. </inglise>
<eesti> HICPde l&auml;bivaatamispoliitika &uuml;lds&auml;tted v&otilde;etakse vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artiklis 14 s&auml;testatud korras, mille j&auml;rel &uuml;leminekumeetmed kaotavad kehtivuse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Entry into force </inglise>
<eesti> J&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the 20th day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kahek&uuml;mnendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
